# Phase 1: Analyze the Fix

This is a patch for Coroutines:

Reland "[CoroCleanup] Noop coroutine elision for load-and-call pattern (#179154)"
There are multiple def-use paths from `coro.noop` to the calls of the resume/destroy functions. We should update the worklist before erasing instructions. The reversion passed tests with ASan enabled.

Reland #179154, which was reverted in #179289 due to ASan failures.

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Coroutines/CoroCleanup.cpp b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Coroutines/CoroCleanup.cpp
